observe.desc:
[
{“Do you know what a genotype and a phenotype are?  Even if the genotypes of two or more biological individuals are exactly the same, they may exhibit different phenotypes. The converse is also true: different combinations of genotypes can have nearly identical phenotypes under certain conditions. What would happen if you modified those genotypes and phenotypes? Altered them? You could make a theoretically ‘perfect’ being. This is a soul that has benefited from such genetic modifications, a one-in-ten-thousand rare individual. Beautiful, isn't it?"}
]

[
{The individual before you cannot even be called a "living being". It is a purely genetic superposition, a life form in the shape of a human, the only individual in the world like it. The creatures born with it are nothing more than a collection of eliminated heterozygotes and recessive individuals, not even remotely close to this perfect creation. The imperfects. The leftovers. Mockeries and forgeries in comparison to its splendor.}
]

[
{They display the perfect products of their cultivation in the window, adorned with silks and satins, standing in shining light, carefully polishing the pearls of the collection. They were clamped between layers of affection until they could no longer breathe. Take a breath at the sight of it, highlight its rarity and preciousness with the bones of its ugly brethren, stomp its forsaken phenotype underfoot, cursing the dirt covering it, and hold the precious jewel on the altar to enjoy all the praise and glory that awaits. But soon enough, the next generation arrives, and with it the effervescence of beauty that shatters against it,  giving birth to a new chapter of beauty--}
]

[
{So the thing died. It shines as an artificial pearl within our hearts.}
]
